defined.

\item[(2)] $X$ is said to have {\it pure projective dimension} at most $n$, written ${\mathop{\rm p.pd}\nolimits}_{R}X\leq n$, if there exists a pure
projective resolution $P\rightarrow X$ with $P^{i}=0$ for any $i<-n$. If ${\mathop{\rm p.pd}\nolimits} _{R}X\leq n$ for all $n$, then we write
${\mathop{\rm p.pd}\nolimits} _{R}X=-\infty$; and if there exists no $n$ such that
${\mathop{\rm p.pd}\nolimits} _{R}X\leq n$, then we write ${\mathop{\rm p.pd}\nolimits} _{R}X=\infty$. Dually, the
{\it pure injective dimension} ${\mathop{\rm p.id}\nolimits}_{R}X$ of $X$ is defined.
\end{enumerate}}
\end{definition}

